<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
        It is common practice to make any language extensible such that one can refine and grow its concepts
        in ways which are relevant for certain applications of such a language. UML supports the specification of
        profiles which represent extension packages containing the language extensions as stereotypes.
    </para>
</section>